        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-10T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="464" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d464">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/12–645: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Murray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-10T18:00:00-05:00">December 10, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>709. Appreciate comments contained in 1082, Dec 6 which are extremely helpful.
                    Our communications with you continue to be hampered by slowness in transmission
                    of messages. Your 1082 arrived in Washington only on morning Dec 9. We are
                    following suggestion made in penultimate paragraph of your 1082. Suggest that
                    all telegrams of any urgency be marked urgent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
